ngs together various migration experiences and national contexts under the same analytical framework to create a rich portrait of the diversity of contemporary Chinese migration processes. By examining the convergence of multiple migration pathways across one geographical region over time, Ho offers alternative approaches to studying migration, migrant experience, and citizenship, thus setting the stage for future scholarship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aChinese diaspora. 0aChinesezForeign countries. 0aCitizenshipzChina. 4aChinese diaspora. 4aalterity. 4aco-ethnics. 4adiaspora strategies. 4adiasporic descendants. 4aextraterritorial citizenship. 4alife course. 4amigrant integration. 4amigration and diversity. 4atransnational migration. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503607460zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503607460423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503607460.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles